Coronavirus in England

These tables show Covid-19 cases and deaths in each local authority (down to district level) across England and each of the four UK nations.

Figures were updated on 28 October and come from the government’s coronavirus dashboard

Contents:
  • Cases: Local authority analysis
  • Deaths: Local authority analysis
  • Cases: Nations analysis
  • Cases: Weekly analysis

Please direct any queries to Rob England, from the BBC England Data Unit

Cases: Local authority analysis

This table shows the number of new coronavirus cases in each local authority (down to district level) in the latest week compared with the week before and the rate per 100,000 population.

Local authorities have been matched where possible to BBC regions but each area is only matched to one region.

We exclude the most recent two days, which will almost certainly be incomplete as not all test results have come back. Data for the most recent few days may change.

Colleagues in the East, South, West and Yorkshire should put ‘BBC’ before their region (e.g. ‘BBC South’) to avoid results from other areas.

PLEASE NOTE ‘latest week’ is the seven days up to and including 25 October.

PLEASE NOTE ‘previous week’ is the seven days up to and including 18 October.

Deaths: Local authority analysis

This table shows the total raw numbers of reported deaths in each area as of today, since the start of the pandemic, and the change since yesterday and last week.

Authorities are ordered by the largest increase since last week.

Deaths figures are not weighted by population.

Figures are for people who died within 28 days of a positive Covid-19 test.

New deaths may have occurred at any point but are newly reported – they did not necessarily die in the last few days.

If figures have gone down this may be due to PHE/DHSC removing duplicates or other revisions.

PLEASE NOTE ‘Change since yesterday’ column is comparing the change in deaths between 27 and 28 of October

PLEASE NOTE ‘Change since last week’ column is comparing the change in deaths between 21 and 28 of October

Cases: Nations analysis

We have also included cases numbers and rates per 100,000 population for each of the four UK nations overall.

PLEASE NOTE ‘latest week’ is the seven days up to and including 25 October.

PLEASE NOTE ‘previous week’ is the seven days up to and including 18 October.
